The problem with this statement is the words &quot;just as&quot;, because the two aren't really comparable.  The warrior beating your trackers to the Quillmane spawn is highly improbable without the help of the Psychic Friends Network.  Becoming an GM in a tradeskill is many times more likely to occur naturally -- because there are some tradeskills where it's not that hard (jc), and because an alarmingly high portion of the player base is demented.<br>
If you were to claim the statement (such as: to people with 2k+, or people who have GM'd X skills in the last 6 months), I might agree with you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub27.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=quirtevans>QuirtEvans</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:pink;'>Tavern Floor Sweeper</span></span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(3/12/03 4:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3159.topic&index=64>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Now THAT's Entertainment</span><hr size=1> &quot;because an alarmingly high portion of the player base is demented&quot;<br>
